ULCANS is a multispectral, lightweight and easy-to-handle camouflage screen that presents a revolution in concealing military objects – to achieve perfect protection while in static position. The product is available in both woodland and desert versions.

COVERS ALL KNOWN SENSOR THREATS

ULCANS represents the most advanced camouflage technology available on the market today. It has multispectral capabilities throughout its service life, enhancing force survivability by providing protection against visual, as well as near-infrared, thermal infrared and broad-band radar threats.

ULTRA LIGHTWEIGHT NON-SNAGGING CONSTRUCTION

ULCANS is the state-of-the-art in screen camouflage. It is non-snagging, quickly deployed, and withstands the rigors of field duty.

SAVE MONEY

Being multispectral, the screen makes multiple or single layers of conventional camouflage products for different requirements virtually redundant. Due to its non-snagging properties, its service life is increased substantially in comparison with conventional nets.

FLEXIBILITY

The ULCANS system used by the U.S. Army consists of one hexagonal and one rhomboidal screen, available in both woodland and desert versions. It features a simplified interconnect system and effective shape disrupters.

This one is slightly used but still in great shape. Brand new this system is more than twice this price.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Do you want to sell your gun on Armslist?
location: In the Middle, Ohio, United States
postcontent:
Do you really want to sell your gun on Armslist?  

The first thing you need to do is "Get Real" about your asking price!  No one here will pay retail.  Don't expect to get as much as you paid at "Gander Mountain" or "Bass Pro" or any other retail store.

Research what your model is actually selling for by subscribing to "GunBroker" or other web sites related to guns and doing a search for "Completed Auctions" regarding your model.

Example: Asking $700 for a Glock 17L because they aren't made anymore?  If you do you're research, you'll find Glock has made a new run of these pistols and they retail for under $600.  Many more examples are available for current production guns.

Good luck all!

title: For Sale:  Krebs Kustoms AK scope rail
postcontent:
If youre unfamiliar with this product it is truly awesome. Probably the best way to mount a scope on an ak. Do yourself a favor and look it up.

http://www.krebscustom.com/products/53/Krebs-Custom-AK-Rear-Sight-Rail-System

A lot of scope mounts just replace the dust cover and bolt on. The problem with that is that you can't field strip the rifle without loss of rifle zero. The Krebs mount allows you mount a scope on the rail over the factory dust cover that is rock solid and with a single push of a pin you can pivot the mount up without loss of zero for field stripping or cleaning. When you're done just pivot it back down in push the pin in. Also gives the rifle a longer sight radius for improved accuracy. 

I mounted this rail once and decided to go a different way with my rifle.
